csw.examples.vsliceJava.assembly

Class SetElevationCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • akka.actor.AbstractActor
      • csw.examples.vsliceJava.assembly.SetElevationCommand
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    akka.actor.Actor

    public class SetElevationCommand
extends akka.actor.AbstractActor
    This actor implements the setElevation command. The setElevation command receives an elevation value. In this implementation, the elevation is used as a range distance that is then converted to a state position and sent to the HCD. This command is similar to the move command and would use the move command except for the fact that at the end of the command, the sodium layer state must be set to true, which is not the case with the mvoe command. There is probably a way to refactor this to reuse the move command.
